    "description": "The Tekna live in the northwestern part of the Sahara and are descended from local Imazighen (Berbers) and Arabs who immigrated to the region between the 15th and 17th centuries. This Tekna headdress is made of braided and knotted synthetic hair, though in the past the hairs of a horse’s tail would have been used. Horses, as well as the glass, silver, coral, shell, and hardstone beads that are used to the headdress harken back to the medieval circulation of these valued materials, exemplifying how the legacy of the past continues to impact the present.",
